You are helping build a Next.js 14 App Router application called Cycle Tracker.

Tech stack:
- Next.js with App Router (never use pages/ directory)
- TypeScript
- Prisma 5 ORM with PostgreSQL
- Clerk for authentication
- Tailwind CSS for styling

Project structure:
- No src/ directory. App folder is at root level /app
- Prisma client singleton is at /app/lib/prisma.ts
- API routes go in /app/api/

Rules:
- All API routes must use auth() from @clerk/nextjs/server
- Always look up the Prisma User by clerkId before any DB operation
- Users can only access their own data, always filter by userId
- Admin routes must verify role === 'ADMIN' before returning data
- Use server components by default, add "use client" only when needed
- All forms should have loading and error states
- Never hardcode user IDs or emails
